  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can see who viewed your videos if they are shared as part of your Stories or as regular posts (with some limitations). Here\u2019s how you can check:\n\n1. **Instagram Stories**:\n   - After posting a Story, go to your Story by tapping on your profile picture at the top of the feed.\n   - Once your Story is playing, you can swipe up on the screen to view the list of users who have viewed your Story.\n\n2. **Instagram Feed Videos** (Regular Posts):\n   - If you post a video on your feed, you can see the total number of views, but you cannot see the usernames of individual users who viewed the video. \n   - To check the views, tap on the video in your feed and look for the view count (indicated by an eye icon).\n\n3. **IGTV Videos**:\n   - If you upload videos to IGTV, you can also see the total views, but not the users who watched.\n\nCurrently, Instagram does not provide a way to see who viewed your videos on your main feed or IGTV, only in Stories. Keep in mind that newer features might be added, so it\u2019s always a good idea to check for updates in the app.",
